<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sys_script"><sys_script action="DELETE"><abort_action>false</abort_action><access>package_private</access><action_delete>false</action_delete><action_insert>true</action_insert><action_query>false</action_query><action_update>true</action_update><active>true</active><add_message>false</add_message><advanced>true</advanced><change_fields>false</change_fields><client_callable>false</client_callable><collection>x_matsa_tasquatch_billing_project</collection><condition/><description/><execute_function>false</execute_function><filter_condition table="x_matsa_tasquatch_billing_project">dataVALCHANGES^dataISNOTEMPTY^EQ<item endquery="true" field="" goto="false" newquery="false" operator="=" or="false" value=""/></filter_condition><is_rest>false</is_rest><message/><name>Update Record from data</name><order>100</order><priority>100</priority><rest_method/><rest_method_text/><rest_service/><rest_service_text/><rest_variables/><role_conditions/><script><![CDATA[(function executeRule(current, previous /*null when async*/) {

	// Mapping Obj
	var varMappingObj = {
		'active':'is_active',
		'budget_hours':'budget',
		'name':'name',
		'client':'client'
	};
	
	// Data Obj
	var dataObj = JSON.parse(current.data);

	// Map fields
	for ( var key in varMappingObj){
		if(dataObj[varMappingObj[key]]){
			try{
				current[key] = dataObj[varMappingObj[key]].name.toString();
			} catch(err) {
				current[key] = dataObj[varMappingObj[key]].toString();
			}
		}
	}
	
	current.update();
	

})(current, previous);]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>brent.llewellyn</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2018-06-05 03:51:28</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>false</sys_customer_update><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_domain_path>/</sys_domain_path><sys_id>97ab0b34dba25b00497856f3ce96194f</sys_id><sys_mod_count>6</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Update Record from data</sys_name><sys_overrides/><sys_package display_value="Tasquatch" source="x_matsa_tasquatch">ed3b6a4adbb51700497856f3ce961949</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Tasquatch">ed3b6a4adbb51700497856f3ce961949</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_97ab0b34dba25b00497856f3ce96194f</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>brent.llewellyn</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2018-06-12 11:37:10</sys_updated_on><template/><when>after</when></sys_script><sys_translated_text action="delete_multiple" query="documentkey=97ab0b34dba25b00497856f3ce96194f"/></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sys_script"><sys_script action="DELETE"><abort_action>false</abort_action><access>package_private</access><action_delete>false</action_delete><action_insert>true</action_insert><action_query>false</action_query><action_update>true</action_update><active>true</active><add_message>false</add_message><advanced>true</advanced><change_fields>false</change_fields><client_callable>false</client_callable><collection>x_matsa_tasquatch_time_entry</collection><condition/><description/><execute_function>false</execute_function><filter_condition table="x_matsa_tasquatch_time_entry">dataVALCHANGES^dataISNOTEMPTY^EQ<item endquery="true" field="" goto="false" newquery="false" operator="=" or="false" value=""/></filter_condition><is_rest>false</is_rest><message/><name>Update Record from data</name><order>100</order><priority>100</priority><rest_method/><rest_method_text/><rest_service/><rest_service_text/><rest_variables/><role_conditions/><script><![CDATA[(function executeRule(current, previous /*null when async*/) {
	var processingNotes = "Started: "+ new GlideDateTime() +"\n";
	// Mapping Obj
	var varMappingObj = {
		'billing_user':'user',
		'hours':'hours',
		'notes':'notes'
	};
	
	// Data Obj
	var dataObj = JSON.parse(current.data);
	
	// find matching Project
	var project_id = dataObj.project.id;
	var project = new GlideRecord('x_matsa_tasquatch_billing_project');
	if(project.get('api_id',project_id)){
		current.billing_project = project.getUniqueValue();
		processingNotes += "\nProject Found: "+ project.name;
	} else {
		processingNotes += "\nProject not Found: "+ project_id;
	}
	// Map fields
	for ( var key in varMappingObj){
		if(dataObj[varMappingObj[key]]){
			try{
				try{
					current[key] = dataObj[varMappingObj[key]].name.toString();
				}catch(err){
					current[key] = dataObj[varMappingObj[key]].toString();
				}
			}catch(err){
				processingNotes += "\nError Mapping Field:"+ key +":"+ varMappingObj[key];
				processingNotes += "\nError:"+ err;
			}
		}
	}
	
	// Find matching User
	if(current.billing_user){
		var user = new GlideRecord('sys_user');
		user.addEncodedQuery('user_name='+current.getValue('billing_user').replace(' ','.')+'^ORname='+current.getValue('billing_user'));
		user.query();
		
		if(user.next()){
			current.user = user.getUniqueValue();
		processingNotes += "\nUser Found: "+ user.name.toString();
		} else {
			processingNotes += "\nUser not Found: "+ current.getValue('billing_user');
		}
	}
	
	// Update Spent Date
	if(dataObj.spent_date){
		current.spent_date = new GlideDateTime(dataObj.spent_date);
		processingNotes += "\nSpent Date Updated.";
	} else {
		processingNotes += "\nSpent Date not Found.";
	}
		
	// submit updates
	
	processingNotes += "\n\nFinished: "+ new GlideDateTime();
	current.processing_notes = processingNotes;
	current.update();
	
	
})(current, previous);]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>brent.llewellyn</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2018-06-04 20:30:54</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>false</sys_customer_update><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_domain_path>/</sys_domain_path><sys_id>6e86e534dbee1b00497856f3ce9619be</sys_id><sys_mod_count>19</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Update Record from data</sys_name><sys_overrides/><sys_package display_value="Tasquatch" source="x_matsa_tasquatch">ed3b6a4adbb51700497856f3ce961949</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Tasquatch">ed3b6a4adbb51700497856f3ce961949</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_6e86e534dbee1b00497856f3ce9619be</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>brent.llewellyn</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2018-06-12 12:33:13</sys_updated_on><template/><when>after</when></sys_script><sys_translated_text action="delete_multiple" query="documentkey=6e86e534dbee1b00497856f3ce9619be"/></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="DELETE"><access>public</access><active>true</active><api_name>x_matsa_tasquatch.messinWithTasquatch</api_name><caller_access/><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>messinWithTasquatch</name><script><![CDATA[var messinWithTasquatch = Class.create();
messinWithTasquatch.prototype = {
    initialize: function() {
        this.harvestApiUrl = 'https://api.harvestapp.com/api/v2/';
    },

    syncOldTasqs: function() {
        var taskImportObj = {};
        var tasqImportRec = new GlideRecord('x_matsa_tasquatch_tasq_import');
        tasqImportRec.addQuery('active', true);
        tasqImportRec.query();
        while (tasqImportRec.next()) {

            var out_of_syncThresholdSeconds = tasqImportRec.out_of_sync_threshold_in_minutes * -60;
            var outOfSyncThreshold = new GlideDateTime(tasqImportRec.last_sync);
            outOfSyncThreshold.addSeconds(out_of_syncThresholdSeconds);

            taskImportObj[tasqImportRec.getUniqueValue()] = {
                'import': tasqImportRec.getUniqueValue(),
                'out_of_syncThreshold': outOfSyncThreshold,

            }

        }

        // Loop through imports to find out of sync tasqs
        for (var taskImport in taskImportObj) {
            var tasq = new GlideRecord('x_matsa_tasquatch_tasquatch');
            tasq.addEncodedQuery("last_sync<=" + taskImportObj[taskImport].out_of_syncThreshold + "^tasq_import=" + taskImportObj[taskImport].import+'^tasquatch_status=in_sync');
            tasq.query();

            while (tasq.next()) {

                this.syncTasq(tasq, 'not_syncing')
            }
        }
    },

    syncTasq: function(tasq, successStatus) {
        var endpoints = {},
            runTime = new GlideDateTime();

        // Get  Endpoint
        var endpointRec = new GlideRecord('x_matsa_tasquatch_endpoints');
        if (endpointRec.get(tasq.getValue('endpoint'))) {

            //Get Tasq Import
            var tasqImportRec = new GlideRecord('x_matsa_tasquatch_tasq_import');
            if (tasqImportRec.get(tasq.getValue('tasq_import'))) {

                // Build object for use in fetching record
                endpoints[tasq.getUniqueValue()] = {
                    'remote_instance': endpointRec.remote_instance + '',
                    'user_name': endpointRec.user_name + '',
                    'password': endpointRec.password.getDecryptedValue() + '',
                    'sys_id': endpointRec.getUniqueValue() + '',
                    "tasqImports": {}
                };

                // Build query info
                endpoints[tasq.getUniqueValue()].tasqImports[tasqImportRec.getUniqueValue()] = {
                    'sys_id': tasqImportRec.getUniqueValue() + '',
                    'table_name': tasqImportRec.table_name + '',
                    'table_query': 'sys_id=' + tasq.tasq_sys_id,
                    'tasq_name': tasqImportRec.tasq_name + ''
                };
                // Get the recs

                var tasqs = this.getTasqs(endpoints[tasq.getUniqueValue()], endpoints[tasq.getUniqueValue()].tasqImports[tasqImportRec.getUniqueValue()]);

                var tasqsObj = JSON.parse(tasqs);
                var endpoint = tasq.getUniqueValue()

                for (var tasq in tasqsObj.result) {

                    this.updateTasqs(tasqsObj.result[tasq], endpoints[endpoint], endpoints[endpoint].tasqImports[tasqImportRec.getUniqueValue()], successStatus);
                }

            } else {
                // Error getting Tasq Import REc
                gs.error('Error getting Tasq Import Rec')
            }
        } else {
            // Error getting Endpoint
            gs.error('Error getting Endpoint')
        }
    },

    syncTasqs: function() {

        var endpointArr = [],
            endpoints = {},
            runTime = new GlideDateTime();
        // Get all Endpoints
        var endpointRec = new GlideRecord('x_matsa_tasquatch_endpoints');
        endpointRec.addQuery('active', true);
        endpointRec.query();
        while (endpointRec.next()) {
            endpoints[endpointRec.getUniqueValue()] = {
                'remote_instance': endpointRec.remote_instance + '',
                'user_name': endpointRec.user_name + '',
                'password': endpointRec.password.getDecryptedValue() + '',
                'sys_id': endpointRec.getUniqueValue() + '',
                'tasqImports': {}
            };

            endpointArr.push(endpointRec.getUniqueValue());
        }

        // Get all Imports for each endpoint
        var tasqImportRec = new GlideRecord('x_matsa_tasquatch_tasq_import');
        tasqImportRec.addQuery('active', true);
        tasqImportRec.addEncodedQuery('endpoint.sys_idIN' + endpointArr.join());
        tasqImportRec.query();
        while (tasqImportRec.next()) {

            var currRun = new GlideDateTime().getNumericValue();
            var lastRun = new GlideDateTime(tasqImportRec.last_sync).getNumericValue();
            var syncInterval = tasqImportRec.sync_interval_in_minutes;
            var currInterval = (currRun - lastRun) / 1000 / 60;

            if (parseInt(currInterval) > parseInt(syncInterval)) {

                endpoints[tasqImportRec.endpoint + ''].tasqImports[tasqImportRec.getUniqueValue()] = {
                    'sys_id': tasqImportRec.getUniqueValue() + '',
                    'table_name': tasqImportRec.table_name + '',
                    'table_query': tasqImportRec.table_query + '',
                    'tasq_name': tasqImportRec.tasq_name + '',
                    'project': tasqImportRec.getValue('project') + ''
                };
                tasqImportRec.last_sync = new GlideDateTime();
                tasqImportRec.update();
            }
        }


        for (var endpoint in endpoints) {

            for (var tasqImport in endpoints[endpoint].tasqImports) {

                if (endpoints[endpoint].tasqImports[tasqImport].table_name) {
                    // Get the recs
                    var tasqs = this.getTasqs(endpoints[endpoint], endpoints[endpoint].tasqImports[tasqImport]);

                    var tasqsObj = JSON.parse(tasqs);

                    for (var tasq in tasqsObj.result) {

                        this.updateTasqs(tasqsObj.result[tasq], endpoints[endpoint], endpoints[endpoint].tasqImports[tasqImport]);
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    },

    getTasqsNow: function(tasqImportRec) {
        var endpointRec = tasqImportRec.endpoint
        endpoint = {
            'remote_instance': tasqImportRec.endpoint.remote_instance + '',
            'user_name': tasqImportRec.endpoint.user_name + '',
            'password': tasqImportRec.endpoint.password.getDecryptedValue() + '',
            'sys_id': tasqImportRec.endpoint.sys_id + '',
            'tasqImport': {}
        };

        endpoint.tasqImport = {
            'sys_id': tasqImportRec.getUniqueValue() + '',
            'table_name': tasqImportRec.table_name + '',
            'table_query': tasqImportRec.table_query + '',
            'tasq_name': tasqImportRec.tasq_name + '',
            'project': tasqImportRec.project.sys_id + ''
        };

        gs.info('getTasqsNow.endpoint: '+ JSON.stringify(endpoint))

        var tasqs = this.getTasqs(endpoint, endpoint.tasqImport);

        var tasqsObj = JSON.parse(tasqs);
        for (var tasq in tasqsObj.result) {
            this.updateTasqs(tasqsObj.result[tasq], endpoint, endpoint.tasqImport);
        }


    },

    getTasqs: function(endPoint, tasqImport) {
gs.info(encodeURI("https://" + endPoint.remote_instance + ".service-now.com/api/now/table/" + tasqImport.table_name + "?sysparm_query=" + tasqImport.table_query.toString() + '&sysparm_display_value=all'))
        var request = new sn_ws.RESTMessageV2();
        request.setEndpoint(encodeURI("https://" + endPoint.remote_instance + ".service-now.com/api/now/table/" + tasqImport.table_name + "?sysparm_query=" + tasqImport.table_query.toString() + '&sysparm_display_value=all'));
        request.setHttpMethod('GET');

        var user = endPoint.user_name;
        var password = endPoint.password;

        request.setBasicAuth(user, password);
        request.setRequestHeader("Accept", "application/json");

        var response = request.execute();
        var respBody = response.getBody();

        return respBody;
    },

    updateTasqs: function(tasq, endPoint, tasqImport, successStatus) {
        var updatedTask = false;
        var relatedRecord = "https://" + endPoint.remote_instance + ".service-now.com/" + tasq.sys_class_name.value + ".do?sys_id=" + tasq.sys_id.value;
        var tasqRec = new GlideRecord('x_matsa_tasquatch_tasquatch');

        gs.info("updateTasqs.tasq: " + JSON.stringify(tasq))
        // If the tasq has previously been mapped update the object only
        if (tasqRec.get('related_record', relatedRecord)) {
            tasqRec.task_obj = JSON.stringify(tasq);
            tasqRec.last_sync = new GlideDateTime();
            tasqRec.project = tasqImport.project;
            if (successStatus)
                tasqRec.tasquatch_status = successStatus;

            updatedTask = tasqRec.update();
        }

        // If the tasq has not previously been mapped create a new Tasq 
        else {
            tasqRec.initialize();
            tasqRec.type = tasq.sys_class_name.display_value;
            tasqRec.related_record = relatedRecord;
            tasqRec.task_obj = JSON.stringify(tasq);
            tasqRec.endpoint = endPoint.sys_id;
            tasqRec.tasq_import = tasqImport.sys_id;
            tasqRec.project = tasqImport.project;
            tasqRec.tasq_sys_id = tasq.sys_id.value;
            tasqRec.last_sync = new GlideDateTime();
            tasqRec.tasquatch_status = 'in_sync';
            updatedTask = tasqRec.insert();
        }
        return updatedTask;
    },

    harvestAPI: function(restMethod, restEndpoint) {

        var accountID = gs.getProperty('x_matsa_tasquatch.harvestAPI.accountID');
        var apiToken = gs.getProperty('x_matsa_tasquatch.harvestAPI.apiToken');
        var requestBody = "";

        try {
            var request = new sn_ws.RESTMessageV2();

            request.setEndpoint(restEndpoint);
            request.setHttpMethod(restMethod);

            request.setRequestHeader("Accept", "application/json");
            request.setRequestHeader('Harvest-Account-ID', accountID);
            request.setRequestHeader('Authorization', 'Bearer ' + apiToken);

            var response = request.execute();

            return {
                'status': response.getStatusCode(),
                'body': JSON.parse(response.getBody())
            };

        } catch (err) {
            return {
                'status': 'Rest Error',
                'error': err
            };
        }
        return false;

    },

    harvestSyncProjects: function() {

        // Sync Projects
        gs.info('Sync Projects')
        this.harvestPullRecs('projects', 'x_matsa_tasquatch_billing_project')

        // Sync Time Entries
        gs.info('Sync Time Entries')
        this.harvestPullRecs('time_entries', 'x_matsa_tasquatch_time_entry')

    },

    harvestPullRecs: function(apiName, syncTable) {

        var respArrLen = 1;
        var pageIndex = 1;
        while (respArrLen > 0 && pageIndex <= 200) {
            var myEndpoint = this.harvestApiUrl + apiName + "?page=" + pageIndex;
            var myHttpMethod = 'GET';
            var response = this.harvestAPI('GET', myEndpoint);

            var respObj = response.body[apiName];
            respArrLen = respObj.length

            pageIndex++;

            // for each rec returned update the corralating snow rec
            for (var entry in respObj) {
                this.syncSnowRec(syncTable, respObj[entry]);
            }
        }
    },

    syncSnowRec: function(table, variableObj) {

        var apiId = variableObj.id
        var gr = new GlideRecord(table);
        if (gr.get('api_id', apiId)) {
            gr.data = JSON.stringify(variableObj);
            gr.update();
        } else {
            gr.initialize();
            gr.api_id = variableObj.id;
            gr.data = JSON.stringify(variableObj);
            gr.insert();
        }
    },

    type: 'messinWithTasquatch'
};]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>brent.llewellyn</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2018-05-24 11:38:03</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>false</sys_customer_update><sys_id>75124f45db9e53005dbe38f0ad961917</sys_id><sys_mod_count>78</sys_mod_count><sys_name>messinWithTasquatch</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Tasquatch" source="x_matsa_tasquatch">ed3b6a4adbb51700497856f3ce961949</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Tasquatch">ed3b6a4adbb51700497856f3ce961949</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_75124f45db9e53005dbe38f0ad961917</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>brent.llewellyn</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2018-09-18 17:11:52</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

sys_update_xml.name: sys_script_2b44b893dbea5f00497856f3ce9619f1
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sys_script"><sys_script action="DELETE"><abort_action>false</abort_action><access>package_private</access><action_delete>false</action_delete><action_insert>true</action_insert><action_query>false</action_query><action_update>true</action_update><active>true</active><add_message>false</add_message><advanced>true</advanced><change_fields>false</change_fields><client_callable>false</client_callable><collection>x_matsa_tasquatch_time_entry</collection><condition/><description/><execute_function>false</execute_function><filter_condition table="x_matsa_tasquatch_time_entry">hoursVALCHANGES^EQ<item endquery="true" field="" goto="false" newquery="false" operator="=" or="false" value=""/></filter_condition><is_rest>false</is_rest><message/><name>Update Billing Project with hours spent</name><order>100</order><priority>100</priority><rest_method/><rest_method_text/><rest_service/><rest_service_text/><rest_variables/><role_conditions/><script><![CDATA[(function executeRule(current, previous /*null when async*/) {
	
	// Get assossiated Billing Project
	var billProj = new GlideRecord('x_matsa_tasquatch_billing_project');
	billProj.get(current.getValue('billing_project'));
	
	// Get all Hours under billing Project
	var timeEntries = new GlideRecord('x_matsa_tasquatch_time_entry');
	timeEntries.query('billing_project',current.getValue('billing_project'));
	
	// Total up hours from time entries
	var hoursSpent = 0;
	while (timeEntries.next()){
		hoursSpent += timeEntries.hours;
	}
	
	// Update Billing Project with hours spent.
	billProj.spent_hours = hoursSpent;
	billProj.update();
	
})(current, previous);]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>brent.llewellyn</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2018-06-12 11:25:44</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>false</sys_customer_update><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_domain_path>/</sys_domain_path><sys_id>2b44b893dbea5f00497856f3ce9619f1</sys_id><sys_mod_count>3</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Update Billing Project with hours spent</sys_name><sys_overrides/><sys_package display_value="Tasquatch" source="x_matsa_tasquatch">ed3b6a4adbb51700497856f3ce961949</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Tasquatch">ed3b6a4adbb51700497856f3ce961949</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_2b44b893dbea5f00497856f3ce9619f1</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>brent.llewellyn</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2018-06-12 12:07:46</sys_updated_on><template/><when>after</when></sys_script><sys_translated_text action="delete_multiple" query="documentkey=2b44b893dbea5f00497856f3ce9619f1"/></record_update>
